2. About Jay Z  Shawn Corey Carter mostly known by Jay-Z  He is married to singer Beyoncé Knowles  Has 1 daughter named Blue Ivey Carter  Born on December 4th, 1969 in Brooklyn  American rapper, Entrepreneur, Agent  Owns Brooklyn Nets, own clothing line, record label

3. Early Life  Jay was born in Brooklyn, New York City  Lived in the Marcy Housing Project  His mother Gloria carter raised him  He had 3 siblings  He attended three different high schools  George Westinghouse Career and Tech School (The Notorious B.I.G. and Busta Rhymes)  He never graduated

4. His Rise  began career selling mixtapes and Cd’s out of car  hard work signed label as a hype man  would rap while people were changing  His fan base soon grew larger  Became who he is today

5. Music and Career  many albums have gone platinum (Magna Carta).  won many awards including multiple Grammy awards  Carter has his own clothing line  Is part owner of the Brooklyn Nets  He moved them there  He also owns Roc Nation Sports agency  Robinson Cano, Kevin Durant, C.C. Sabthia  Is a record producer, owns his own record label.  2k14 Music producer
